<taxonomicName authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1821" box="[151,377,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janthinus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,377,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Mecinus janthinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1437,510,750]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[151,265,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Elytra distinctly elongate. Dorsal integument black or blue, sometimes with metallic reflections. Flagellum characterized by at least six rounds. Spermatheca with subspherical body including ramus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1437,510,750]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis box="[199,569,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Remarks and comparative notes.</emphasis>
The shape of the body together with the colour of the dorsal integument are characters which this group shares with that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wencker" authorityYear="1866" box="[717,854,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heydenii">
<emphasis box="[717,854,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. heydenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two groups include the unique species of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,246,655,678]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,246,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Mecinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not living on 
<taxonomicName box="[410,512,654,678]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Plantago" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[410,512,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Plantago</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1821" box="[786,929,654,678]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janthinus">
<emphasis box="[786,929,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. janthinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguishable from those related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wencker" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Mecinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heydenii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">M. heydenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the less curved rostrum in lateral view, the shape of the penis, the distinctly longer flagellum and the completely unusual shape of the spermatheca that is reminiscent of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" box="[949,1036,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cionini">Cionini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
